file_insights.purpose: Tracks build automation state for feature spec 115-build-inspection-history-timeline

patterns_discovered.description: System completes subtasks sequentially, incrementing completion counter and moving through defined phases
patterns_discovered.evidence: completed count increased from 5 to 6 with phase transition

patterns_discovered.description: Build process organized into distinct phases (Frontend - API Integration -> Integration Testing)
patterns_discovered.evidence: phase.current and phase.total both updated in single commit

patterns_discovered.description: Each subtask completion initiates a new numbered session
patterns_discovered.evidence: session.number incremented from 6 to 7 with 3 minute time gap

patterns_discovered.description: Build system limited to 1 active worker with max capacity of 1

gotchas_discovered.description: phase.total decreased from 2 to 1 during build, suggesting dynamic phase planning or scope adjustment
gotchas_discovered.risk: Could indicate incomplete phase enumeration or late discovery of reduced remaining phases

gotchas_discovered.description: Time gap of 3 minutes 3 seconds between session 6 and session 7 updates
gotchas_discovered.risk: Suggests either processing time or scheduled delays between subtask executions

gotchas_discovered.description: workers.active remains 0 despite active subtask processing
gotchas_discovered.risk: Worker counting mechanism may not accurately reflect true execution state

recommendations.recommendation: Implement worker activity logging to explain zero active_workers count despite ongoing subtask processing
Document dynamic phase adjustments - clarify whether phase.total reduction is expected behavior or indicates scope creep management
Investigate 3+ minute gaps between session transitions to identify bottlenecks or intentional delays
Verify end-to-end timeline verification actually ran given single remaining subtask - ensure integration testing phase covers all completion criteria
